    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Fuel System - Removal - Horizontal Fuel
        Conditioning Module (HFCM)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="m4" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Horizontal Fuel Conditioning Module (HFCM)</title>
        <figure id="f3001302.5" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11059.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px" box="no"/>
            <caption>HFCM (chassis mounted)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel supply port to engine</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel return port from engine</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel return port to tank</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel supply port to HFCM</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Electric fuel pump connection</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water In Fuel (WIF) electrical connection</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water drain plug</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting grommet (3)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel heater electrical connection</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Primary filter element cap</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>For CityStar&#8482;applications, the HFCM is mounted on the driver's side vehicle frame rail.</para>
        <para>For stripped chassis applications, the HFCM is mounted on a bracket attached to the transmission housing
            on the passenger side.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a container under the HFCM to drain fuel and any accumulated water.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate water drain plug to release fuel pressure and drain HFCM.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect fuel pump, fuel heater, and Water In Fuel (WIF) electrical connectors.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press in retaining clips to release fuel hoses from HFCM housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect fuel hoses and discard fuel hose retaining clips</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three M8 mounting nuts and remove HFCM from chassis.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
